metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 2 #227
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ - Iteration 1, ____ - Iteration 2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: Elementary Cellular Emoji Automata #192
metadata.description:
Features the full set of 1761 emojis, including skin tone and gender modifiers and all flags.
Arranged using the full 256 ruleset of one-dimensional cellular automata

If “random seed” is true then the seed of the generation is randomized using Math.random() meaning that the pattern will change on regeneration.
The ruleset, emoji, colors and all other properties will remain the same.

Auto-adjusts to screen size

Compatible with as many browsers and systems as possible

metadata.name: Expressive #66
metadata.description:
Expressive is my first generative piece ever. In this piece, I want to allow the randomness to take place. To me, making art is an activity of both freedom and complete control. And by freedom I mean the opposite of controlling the end results – you just let it come, and let it be. I hope you enjoy the random outputs (but controlled by me, lol).

FEATURES:

↳ Backgrounds
White, Black and Random Color

↳ 12 Bases
↳ 25 Tops
↳ Up to 3 painting layers
↳ Noises

Press “s” to save a PNG file.

****

I will select the first 20 mints to receive my next 5 airdrops on Tezos.

****

Thank you so much!
/petrichor3000

metadata.name: Petri 1500 #1368
metadata.description:
Petri 1500 is a celebration of reaching 1500 Twitter followers.
As I've grown as an artist what represents that growth but a petri dish, filled with life, finding a way. 

A sillybration of all things fx(hash) featuring some of my recognisable pallets and primatives
along with something new to me - noise and 'realistic' nature sketches. 
All mashed for pure fun.

L to download 1000x1000
S to download 4000x4000

metadata.name: Flow and Flora #3

Click or Tap the canvas to toggle full screen mode.
